hopobject.body: Another service? fitjoy bars review What it did seem like was a fine day of clay-court tennis, even if neither result was ever in doubt. Coric, fresh from his triumph in the junior US Open, gave notice of his rare talent. He pushed Murray all the way in a first-set performance that would have done credit to a player ranked 52, let alone 525. The match was only a few minutes old when they contested a 57-shot rally. At around a minute long, that would have outlasted any single point in the entire US Open.
